        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 5:53PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 553 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms to the east and southeast of Karval, moving east at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Landspouts and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wild Horse Point.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
